# Things I learned to use with lua

//Glossary:
//
// To recall(1): '*' stands for characters that may come before or after this symbol.
// ==================================================================================
//
// *jit - Just-In-Time, int this context refers to interpreters such as 'luajit' for exemple.
//
// repl - Read, Evaluate, Print and then Loop : Is a command line mode where one may execute commands from
//        a programming language in an interactive environment. Most new programming languages support this feature.
//

1) In order for the lua repl to interpret a escape character such as '!' as a printable one, it must be inside a 
   single quotes string.

   Ex_1:  ~$ luajit -e 'print("Hello World!")'
